<h2 class="bac">Our Business:</h2>
<p class="bac">
The Corporate Debt Products and the Financial Institutions Debt Products groups are responsible for underwriting, originating, and managing the credit and market risks associated with Corporate and Financial Institutions loan and trading portfolios respectively. A wide range of loan classes and structures are underwritten and monitored, including (i) secured and unsecured, (ii) senior and subordinated, (iii) high-yield and investment grade, (iv) bilateral and syndicated, etc. Products traded include credit, interest rates, foreign exchange and equities, together with a wide range of derivative products on these asset classes. The team uses cutting–edge risk management techniques to support our commitment to reduce credit and trading loss volatility. 
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Overview:</h2>  
<p class="bac">
Analysts are involved in: 
</p>
<ul class="bac">	
	<li>Performing intensive qualitative and quantitative due diligence on the client/bank and industry </li>	
	<li>Participating in structuring, underwriting and documentation of syndicated/structured credit facilities </li>	
	<li>Providing recommendations for time sensitive transactional approvals</li>	
	<li>Researching, writing and presenting financial and industry analyses supporting company or financial institutions and portfolio decisions. Plus periodically reassessing internally–assigned risk ratings</li>	
	<li>Evaluating transaction and relationship risk–adjusted profitability to facilitate the allocation of the bank&#39;s capital </li>	
	<li>Monitoring the bank&#39;s credit exposure to its clients across their international networks as well as ours and a substantial suite of products </li>
</ul>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Qualifications:</h2>
<p class="bac">
Candidates must demonstrate a combination of academic aptitude, quantitative skills, strategic and creative thinking and written and oral communications skills. In addition you must have obtained or are realistically expecting to obtain a minimum 2:1 degree or equivalent.
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Training:</h2>
<p class="bac">
Depending on which group successful candidates join training will begin in the US initially with analysts from all lines of business. The programme is a combination of classroom instruction, e-learning modules, case studies and presentations. Throughout the tuition period, analysts have ample opportunities to work closely with professionals and peers across Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America. This is a great opportunity to build a network of colleagues from across the company which will prove to be a tremendous resource throughout your career with the bank.
</p>
<p class="bac">
Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America places a great deal of emphasis on on-going training for all staff. Training modules are available to all levels from product specific courses to generic soft skills development. Whether a new graduate, or seasoned professional, expanding the skills of the associates is paramount to achieving success. Specialized industry training will be principally on-the-job.  
</p>

